parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the vehicle to take longer to stop, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS engages at low speeds
causing the vehicle to lunge forward or increase stopping distance
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle shakes or vibrates when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and failure of brake lines can cause the loss of brake fluid, leading to a loss of braking power, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle has a soft or spongy brake pedal
the vehicle has a loss of brake fluid
the brake lines are corroded or ruptured.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel line can cause fuel leaks, increasing the risk of fires, explosions, and accidents.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the fuel line
the fuel line is corroded or ruptured.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Speed Sensitive Steering (SSS) system can cause the steering wheel to jerk or pull to one side, leading to loss of control, accidents, or near-misses.
symptoms: The steering wheel jerks or pulls to one side
especially during right-hand turns or at moderate speeds; loss of steering feedback; sudden and unpredictable changes in steering resistance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the pitman arm can cause the steering wheel to stick or lock, leading to loss of control, accidents, or near-misses.
symptoms: The steering wheel sticks or locks; difficulty turning the steering wheel; loss of steering control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clockspring can cause the airbag warning indicator to illuminate, potentially leading to airbag deployment failure in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Airbag warning indicator illumination; no other symptoms reported.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle surges or hesitates while driving
the transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
the transmission makes unusual noises or vibrations
the vehicle stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle makes unusual noises or vibrations
the transfer case leaks fluid
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
the vehicle stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driveshaft or axle can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle makes unusual noises or vibrations

the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
the vehicle stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wiring harness or PCM can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
